        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 12 at 6:49PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 648 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 9 miles west of Pigeon to Sebewaing to Akron.
Movement was east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Bad Axe, Sebewaing, Ubly, Caseville, Port Austin, Pigeon, Elkton,
Kinde, Owendale, Verona, Ivanhoe, Rapson, Bay Port, Pinnebog, Port
Crescent State Park, Filion, and Bach.

People attending Cheeseburger Festival in Caseville should seek safe
shelter immediately!
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

These storms may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
